---
title: "auctionCallback (AuctionBidder)"
---
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB
    [*] --> q_guard: whenNotPaused
    q_guard --> q_auth: msg.sender == address(s_auction) AND from == address(this)
    q_auth --> q_revert: false
    q_auth --> q_decode: true
    q_revert --> [*]: revert AccessForbidden()
    q_decode --> q_multicall: calls = abi.decode(data, Call[])
    q_multicall --> q_approve: _multiCall(calls)
    q_approve --> [*]: forceApprove(msg.sender, amountOut)

    note right of q_auth
        INV-001: Only the auction contract can invoke this callback
        INV-002: from must be this contract (bid originated from this contract)
    end note

    note right of q_multicall
        INV-003: _multiCall executes arbitrary external calls decoded from data
        INV-004: Calls must succeed or entire transaction reverts
    end note

    note right of q_approve
        INV-005: After solving, contract approves auction to pull exactly amountOut of assetOut
    end note
